            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#unk">Curtis</note>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Asylum for the Insane,</name>
                    <name type="place">London,</name>
                    <date when="1885-10-02"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>2 Oct <handShift rend="printed"/>188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>5</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I have your card of last Wednesday<ptr target="n5002d"/> I feel greatly concerned at your condition and wish more 
                than ever that you had got up here last spring&#8212;we had such a cool summer here that 
                unquestionably you would have been better here than in Camden. I am very anxious to see you 
                and will do so as soon as I can get away from here&#8212;I think I told you I had four months 
                holidays beginning 15<hi rend="underline">th</hi> of the present month. Shortly after the 
                15<hi rend="underline">th</hi> I hope to see you and then we shall see what can be done. 
                Meantime please write to me as often as you can telling me how you keep.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately yours</salute>
                <signed>R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
